2 What is AI-Driven IaC and why should you care ? :
---------------------------------------------------
    Traditional IAC :                                      AI-Driven IAC  
  manual code writing from scratch                  AI-Assisted code generation
  Consistent documentaion look up                     Context-aware suggetions 
  trial and error debugging                           Automated troubleshooting
  time intensive development process                Rapid prototyping & Iteration 
                                               Natural languages to infrastructre code

In this section, we will understand what AI-Driven Infrastructure as Code means and why it is important for us as DevOps engineers.
We will first look at the traditional way of writing Infrastructure as Code, where we manually write Terraform from scratch. 
In this approach, we spend a lot of time referring to documentation, fixing syntax errors, and using trial-and-error to debug issues. 
While this method works, it is slow and time-consuming, especially when we are learning or experimenting.

Next, we will see how AI-Driven IaC changes this process. Instead of writing everything manually, we use AI to assist us in generating Terraform code. 
AI understands the context of what we are building and provides smart suggestions while we write code. This reduces the need to constantly search documentation and helps us avoid common mistakes.
We will also see how AI helps with troubleshooting, where it can explain errors and suggest fixes, making debugging faster and easier. 
Because of this, we can quickly try different ideas, make changes, and improve our infrastructure without spending too much time on syntax issues.
Another important concept we will learn is how natural language can be converted into infrastructure code. 
This means we can describe our infrastructure requirements in simple English, and AI will generate the corresponding Terraform code for us. 
This makes Infrastructure as Code easier to learn and faster to implement.
Overall, this section helps us understand how AI makes Infrastructure as Code more efficient, more accessible, and more practical for real-world use.
  

